definition: lit. strung through and filled with evil (idiom); filled with extreme evil/replete with vice/guilty of monstrous crimes

sentences.english: That robber is laden with guilt.
The fool fills himself up with evil, even if collecting it just little by little.
sentences.chinese: 如同滴水能注满水瓶，愚人累积小恶至罪恶满盈。

sentences.english: My tears could not help coming.
The moon wax till it become full, and then wane.
sentences.chinese: 月亮渐渐变圆直至满盈，然后再变亏缺。

sentences.english: Of rubies and diamonds, of silver and gold, His coffers are full, He has riches untold.
sentences.chinese: 白玉和碧翠钻石和金银，在父仓库里，积蓄丰富满盈。

sentences.english: And you see tears fall, so the heart has been.
sentences.chinese: 与君一见泪满盈，只因此心已洛印。

sentences.english: The moon rains out her beams, and heaven is overflowed.
sentences.chinese: 射出烟雨般的光柱，天际满盈。

sentences.english: If you had infinite (free) time to yourself what are the three things you would do?
sentences.chinese: 要是有满盈的时间让自已支配，会做哪三件事？

sentences.english: People say orange is a lively, energetic color.
sentences.chinese: 人们说橙色是满盈生机的主动向上的颜色。

sentences.english: Life is chock-full of fun! the key is tsimilarg the time to find it.
sentences.chinese: 生活中满盈了快乐，关键是花些时间徐徐去发现快乐。

definition: to be full to overflowing/to be brimming over with
lit. pile up gold and jade/very rich
congestion/to block/to congest/to crowd/to choke/to cram/to fill up/to stuff/to take up all the space
to sprout up/to flourish/(of war etc) to break out/rapid growth
profits pouring in from all sides (idiom)/raking in money/bonanza
to well up/to spill out (of water from a spring)
to grow without restraint/overflowing with/to happen unexpectedly
(of a perfume or a foul odor) permeating the whole place/(of grease etc) dripping everywhere/flowing all over the place
